column3: Please read the tab "How to fill in the form" for more information on how to complete the sample submission form.
column11: If filled in, leave column I and J blank.
column23: If project will go in R&D workflow, all these fields MUST be filled in!
OPTIONAL: You may fill in these columns, and Clarity will use the info from the sample form instead of "project level info" from Clarity

column1: Label your plate exactly as automatically generated in column A. NOTE! Don´t forget to fill in your project code in the "Sample information" tab
column3: Pool# that the library in column D belongs to. See dropdown for options (possible to drag to fill down).
column4: Name of the library in the pool. Only a-z, A-Z, 0-9, and - (dash) are allowed characters. No whitespaces!
column5: Plate well position of libraries in column D. Several libraries can be in the same well if you are submitting a pool. Libraries must be placed columnwise starting at A1, B1 etc. No empty wells between samples!
column6: Choose "96 well plate" if 96-well plate. Choose "tube" if 1.5 ml Eppenorf tubes. Tubes may only be used if less than 8 samples.
column7: Sample concentration (ng/ul). If your libraries are pooled, state the total concentration of the pool on each sample row.
column8: Library volume (µl). If your libraries are pooled, state the total volume of the pool on each sample row. Sample volume must be 25-50 µl!
column9: Select index type (dropdown). NOTE! If the index kit is not specified, fill in column K instead ("CUSTOM INDEX").
column10: Select index number (see separate Index tab). NOTE! If not applicable, fill in column K instead ("CUSTOM INDEX").
column11: You may specify the exact index sequence here, instead of column I-J. Use the following format for dual index (i7-i5): NNNNNNNN-NNNNNNNN.                 Use the following format for Chromium single-index: NNNNNNNN|NNNNNNNN|NNNNNNNN|NNNNNNNN Note! No bar at the end of the Chromium indices.
column12: Double-check the information in this column with your library preparation manual. Duplicates are highlighted in red. As long as the duplicates are in different pools, this is OK.
column13: Date when samples were delivered in format YYMMDD. The plate should be labelled with the information in column A (from user) + date.
column14: Sample type is "Ready-made library" for this sample form
column15: In Clarity, plates with all submitted libraries in pools will be created and thereafter pools are made in the user interface. The well position below is not the true well postition if libraries are in pools.
column16: Current sample volume. Automatically filled in based on column "Volume"
column17: Total amount of sample. This column is for "sanity check". If possible, return ORG-plate to user if concentrations are too high. See INS-01465 for requirments and max allowed concentrations for DNA/RNA
column18: Plate number, used to generate Plate barcode in column "Container ID"
column19: Plate barcode: ProjectID_PLx_org_YYMMDD. Automatically filled in based on "Sample information" tab and cols "Plate" and "Date sample delivery"
column20: Date Sample Delivery in Clarity friendly format. Automatically filled in based on Date Sample Delivery. YYYY-MM-DD
column21: Kit/method used for library preparation. Automatically filled in based on "Sample information" tab. If the information is not stated, the value "RML" is added by default.
column22: See dropdown for options. Default is "To be decided …". For specific information about concentration on flowcell, see INS-32721.
column23: See UDF "Species" in  "CUSTOM FIELDS" for project in Clarity.
column24: See dropdown for options. See UDF "Application" in "CUSTOM FIELDS" for project in Clarity
column25: Default is NO. If YES, special information is required for post-QC or sequencing (e.g. custom primer, odd read-length). A file must already be uploaded under project details: "Projektkod_special_info_seq" or "Projektkod_special_info_QC-post"
column26: Default for this field is NO. If YES, special information is required for bioinfo analysis. A file must already be uploaded under project details in Clarity: "Projektkod_special_info_bio".
column27: Number of libraries to be pooled together in sequencing. If pooling required, use "number of libraries in project" / "number of lanes or flowcells in project". Example: 24 libraries to be sequenced on 2 lanes = 12 libraries/pool
column28: Number of lanes or flowcells per pool to be sequenced. If pooled libraries OR individual un-pooled libraries: "xx lane/pool". If full NovaSeq or MiSeq flowcell: "xx flowcell/pool"
column29: See dropdown for options, do not insert %. See UDF "Low complexity library" in "CUSTOM FIELDS" for  project in Clarity. Default is 1%. RAD/GBS: 10%. Mehtylation: 5-10%. Amplicon: 10%.
column30: See dropdown for options. See UDF "Sequencing instrument" in "CUSTOM FIELDS" for project in Clarity
column31: See dropdown for options. See UDF "Read length bp" in "CUSTOM FIELDS" for project in Clarity
column32: See dropddown for options. If YES, information about the primer and a protocol for the primer should be uploaded to the project. See col "Special info sequencing" in this form.
